WorkItem.Description:
For example, using the following code:

```ts
declare class A {
	static foo;
}
declare class B extends A {
	static bar;
}
declare class C extends B {
	static baz;
}

C.baz;
C.bar;
```

If I then type `C.f` I should expect to see `foo` show up as a possible property, but I don't, because Intellisense only works 2 levels deep.

Issue presents itself both in the playground as well as in Visual Studio.

[Playground here](http://www.typescriptlang.org/Playground/#src=declare%20class%20A%20%7B%0A%09static%20foo%3B%0A%7D%0Adeclare%20class%20B%20extends%20A%20%7B%0A%09static%20bar%3B%0A%7D%0Adeclare%20class%20C%20extends%20B%20%7B%0A%09static%20baz%3B%0A%7D%0A%0AC.baz%3B%0AC.bar%3B%0A)
